OL,4,CHate crimes on police 'more likely to
OL,5,Cbe charged'
OL,6, Police officers reporting hateful abuse
OL,7, while on duty are much more likely than
OL,8, members of the public to see their
OL,9, attackers charged with hate crime,
OL,10, according to an investigation by BBC
OL,11, Newsnight and the Law Society Gazette.
OL,13,FThe new figures, obtained under the
OL,14,FFreedom of Information Act from some of
OL,15,Fthe largest forces in England, show
OL,16,Fthat police officers and staff were the
OL,17,Fvictims in up to half of the hate
OL,18,Fcrimes charged in some areas, despite
OL,19,Fmaking up a tiny proportion of the
OL,20,Foverall number of recorded cases. The
OL,21,Fvast majority are serving officers.
